<br />
<span style="color: violet">Magician – Update scheduled for 10/22/04</span>
<br />
<span style="color: green"> 
<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">Personal note to the developers:</span></span> The #1 area that the Magician community would like to see a response from the developers is the return of the days when the mage could depend on our pet as a viable source of dps/defense for the content the we are fighting. Specifically this changed regarding pet scaling in PoP, GoD and OoW.
<br />
 
<br />
Due to the fact that at lvl 58 and higher a magician could no longer count on the necessary dps/defensive abilities that their pet had provided them from lvls 4-57, there is a severe gap in our ability to be useful in a group or be a true soloing class beyond that level.
<br />
 
<br />
Please review item #1 on our list as the most important item to the mage community. This one area when resolved will fix 95% of all of the class balancing requests of the mage community. We have taken polls on the subject and roughly 70% of mages agree that fixing broken pets and improving our pets DPS/survivability(with pets being our only source of defense) is the only issue that truly matters.
<br />
 
<br />
<span style="color: blue"><span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">1.Improve pets-</span> </span> <span style="color: red">Currently being discussed</span>
<br />
 
<br />
-Damage ability Improve overall pet DPS for PoP, GoD, and OoW pets.
<br />
 
<br />
-Survivability/Defense upgrade
<br />
a)Elemental immunities have been broken since they were changed (how pets resist spells) about 2 years ago, it is still broken. We should return the elementals immunity to their element (the same reason why mobs in Pofire are immune to our fire nukes).
<br />
 
<br />
b)Pet mitigation isn't terrible on baseline pets, but should scale much more based on what focus is being used. (A Tavici war is going to mitigate a TON better than an LDoN war, neglecting the massive hp and dps advantage he'll also have). All aspects of pets performance should scale the same way, not just boosts to hp, regen and dps.
<br />
 
<br />
-Pet Utility- Restore four distinct and fully-functional pets. 
<br />
a)Rathe's Son and Child of Earth – Remove the proximity agro that root causes which makes our earth pet undesirable in groups and on raids.Possible solution:Re-code Earth Elemental Strike with proximity agro component removed.
<br />
 
<br />
b)Fix our lvl 51 and higher fire pet - This pet has been broken for four years. It is so bad that mages can no longer use it. We have made repeated requests for fire pets to be fixed. We have presented several solutions, please address and complete this issue.
<br />
 
<br />
-Upgrade our summoned focus items, pet armor and weapons - <span style="color: orange">our brand new OoW pet weapons do no additional damage than the PoP era summoned weapons. (example spear of the deep/blade of the kedge). </span>Summoned pet only items should have new procs like slow, snarelure and rune.
<br />
 
<br />
2. <span style="color: blue">Improve pet heals</span> <span style="color: green">Currently being evaluated</span>
<br />
 
<br />
-Shorter cast times and shorter recast times
<br />
 
<br />
-Have our pet focus (DPOC, MoD, MoE, MoDis, Ritual Summoning) also enhance pet heals
<br />
 
<br />
-Increase heal amount
<br />
 
<br />
-Give us a heal over time spell
<br />
 
<br />
<span style="color: blue">3.Revamp pet focus, availability and drop rates</span> <span style="color: red">Currently being discussed</span>
<br />

<br />
-Give casual players and family guilds a way to obtain, quest or upgrade beyond the level of Summoner's boon. (MoD, MoE)
<br />

<br />
-Improve pet gains (especially DPS) with higher-level pet focus pieces. Pet focus should scale better with OoW era content.
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: blue">4. COTH utility</span> <span style="color: red">Currently being discussed</span>
<br />
 
<br />
-Make CoTH available in all corpse summoning, druid 0% rez zones. If a small area of the zone is necessary to have coth, corpse summon, druid 0% rez blocked for potential exploit reasons then just block that small area of the zone.
<br />
 
<br />
-Create a cross zone coth ability.
<br />
 
<br />
<span style="color: blue">5. Update Rains</span> <span style="color: red">Currently being discussed</span>
<br />
 
<br />
-Our high end OoW rains cannot be chain casted. Please remove the grey out blocker/locker on the casting times.
<br />
 
<br />
-Remove the innate resists on Rains, and retune the mana cost on many rains See <a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/editorials/rains.html" target="_blank">http://www.magecompendium.com/editorials/rains.html</a> for details.
<br />

<br />
6.defer to #1 Improve pets
<br />
7.defer to #1 Improve pets
<br />
8.defer to #1 Improve pets
<br />
9.defer to #1 Improve pets
<br />
10.defer to #1 Improve pets
<br />
 
<br />
Note to PvP correspondent/developers: This item is on the PvP top 10 issues list, see here for details, <a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=5933" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=5933</a>
<br />
 
<br />
-Have pets be treated like PC’s instead of NPC’s for spell resists, damage, etc. See this link for detail: <a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=16550&highlight" target="_blank">http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=16550&highlight</a>
<br />
 
<br />
Note: Items set to go live soon, but held up: <span style="color: green">Submitted this suggestion to dev</span>
<br />
 
<br />
-Making pet be able to survive invisibility - <span style="color: green">Done</span>
<br />
-Targeted summons to hit live server. (possible interm solution make it just for pets until the code is developed for players to refuse?)
<br />
<span style="font-size: 24px; line-height: normal"></span><br />_________________<br /><img src="http://members.cox.net/dtresendes/danisig.png" border="0" />
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=639739" target="_blank" class="postlink">Danille Impholder</a>
<br />
Ayonae Ro ~ Vallis Aspectus
<br />
Keep Norrath Safe</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
