			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I don't post a lot but this post and the recent weeks have me motivated again about 'Mage Issues'.
<br />

<br />
Let talk about pet pathing again. I see that this is something that just cant be fixed. I have been soloing in Nobles Causeway. This is a brand new zone and the pathing problems shouldn't exist, but they DO! If I pull a mob with malosinia and use /pet hold (so that my pet doesn't peel off and attack, just in case the mob casts on me) that pet should be at my side as I run back to a spot where I am not going to get adds. I run off and turn to face the enemy /pet attack. "Attacking <insert monster name> master" but: No pet? Where is the pet? "A monster hits Kshipper fro 664dmg!" "A monster kicks Kshipper for 330dmg" and so on. Where is pet? Oh..there he is coming from the direction I just came from playing along the wall. Grrrrr. It doesn't happen all the time but it happens enough that I have to leave pet at the camp to insure it is there when I get back. I think that blows. I like my pet at my side. Once in a while I safely cast on mobs in Nobles to pull and they warp on my head, which means the appear and hit me immediately! Stun stun stun and my pet at my side would very handy in those situations.
<br />

<br />
This is my suggestion for a fix for the above. A item/spell/ability that enables you Summon Companian zero cast time. How unbalancing would that be? It wouldn't be! 
<br />

<br />
Once the mob is getting hit. I just cant seem to get them down fast enough. Rains seem to be one of the spells that look like it could put out some damage. I have tried the latest rain Jerikor and boy , is it resisted. When you need your spells to hit you just can't count on Rains. What is with this spell lineup guys? Point Blank AE is more usefull on raids and rains just are not usefull. I was real bored one day and decided, ya' know I never did the clay braclet quest so off I go to Rathe Mountains to find Findlegrob and Bindlegrob etc. Now these guys are like level 25? I decide to use Rain of Jerikor and whipe em all out in one go. Wrong! ALL 3 waves were resisted! WTF!?
<br />

<br />
Remove resist on rains is a must.
<br />

<br />
Fire pet: Mages want to put out more dps. Perhaps this fire pet would cast only and not melee? Like a mini wizard at our side? It would be way cool if we had two pets at the same time and the 2nd one was the fire pet that casts only like those mobs you see in Kod Taz with the two pets. Don't say Host already does this because my hosts always grab aggro and are killed before they get a chance to do damage and the AE on bosses always kills them off even faster.
<br />

<br />
Pet Focus: Thes items are still too rare. I originally wanted Dark Gloves of Summoning but the guild I was in at the time had no desire to go to Vex Thal. Later DPoC comes out on LdoN expansion and that is a god send with its increase in pet power. My eye also falls on a even better focus available as a Aug on a Raid only LdoN encounter. This encounter is widely known to be bugged so no one does it. No new pet focus. Time passes and we finally are Time enabled. We have been in Time and the last 9 kills on Bertox I have not seen the drop that gives the next level of pet focus. =( The guild focus is now on GoD expansion. The Primals drop a Ruby Ring that also has the Time level pet focus on it. I have only seen one drop in all the Primals we killed. There is a Aug on Ikkiniz raid 2 that drops with Time level focus but the only one that did drop was mis-looted by mistake by a warrior and I never saw another, furtermore the guild only does Ikk3 and Ikk4 now and the Aug does not drop there. =( 
<br />
Ritual focus would be even nicer but it drops only beyond Uqua so MORE waiting it seems. Is it me or are pet focus just too rare? I have been playing a Mage for over 5 years. One focus upgrade is all I have ever got and that was available to anyone that cared to earn the LdoN points? Something seems wrong with that.
<br />

<br />
You guys changed the way the Damage Shield spell lasts. Hurray for that. It lasts a lot longer now but you need to change the way the pet mana tap spells work. Hitting my pet for 1200 every 5-6mins is tedious as all get out! It's too often to do that and use rods every 5mins just to much busy work to maintain our mana pools. We did an encounter last night. It was the Monk epic in 7th hammer. That guy has a lot of hps. So I am sending the pet in and I am nuking. I spam Malosinia every other cast so that my DD spells will land. None of my spells were effective and I am level 69. Most of the time they hit quite low (partial resist) or 100 perc resist. The pet needs to be healed because of AE and the pet needs Callaiv to survive the AE better (another mana hog spell) I went OOM before anyone else and the raid was able to take on the same encounter within minutes because CLR can do it by casting a lvl 39 CH spell over and over. I really felt useless since we killed him 5 times I really did squat for damage on that encounter. Something is wrong there.
<br />

<br />
Other then COH for being handy a Mage is just not needed. We really need some killer raid utility guys. Don't suggest rods. most peeps don't even bother with rods anymore. It's too much bother to be forced to only click them outside of a pack and run a egg timer on your desk for the next time 5 mins go by and it use it again.
<br />
 
<br />
Whats with gracing BLs with nice pet heals and tanking ability, slows AND giving them raid utility with bombs? Whats with making Necros the king of solo (taking away the Mage solo ability at level 60) and the NEC have two excellent raid utilities, the abilty to mana pump and feign and rez people.
<br />

<br />
Wiz also solo well with snare and superb damage and raid utility with ports.
<br />

<br />
Mages need a killer raid ability that people don't want to be without. You just need a Mage in any situation the way the game curently is.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=274568" target="_blank" class="postlink">Kshipper Arch Mage</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
