				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You have two incompatible items on the top 10 list and need to figure out which one we want lest SoE decide for us (if any).
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">b)Pet mitigation isn't terrible on baseline pets, but should scale much more based on what focus is being used. (A Tavici war is going to mitigate a TON better than an LDoN war, neglecting the massive hp and dps advantage he'll also have). All aspects of pets performance should scale the same way, not just boosts to hp, regen and dps. 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">-Give casual players and family guilds a way to obtain, quest or upgrade beyond the level of Summoner's boon. (MoD, MoE) 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
If you let casuals get the higher pet focuses, then you cant have the focuses upgraded to match the gear that drops in equivalent zones. Minion of Eternity is a Time (and Yxxta, others) drop so you want the pets to be upgraded to closer to a time geared PC. But you also want a family/casual who will never see Time or be hanging out with Time equiv geared people to be able to quest to raise their pet to that level? It won't work.
<br />

<br />
My opinion is you need to drop the request to have higher focuses questable by casuals. Thats the only way we are going to be able to get the focuses to scale better compared to equiv. geared PCs, and I think thats a far more deseirable upgrade.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
