				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">What I am saying people is that this is broken for casual players as well as for raiding mages. I do attend raids and the pets are broken so I do not want to see a change put in that will only effect the high end of all mages. 
<br />

<br />
Simply put I pay my $12.95 a month just like all of you raiding mages. So just because I have a busy life and can not be in a guild that wants you to raid 4-6 hours a day I am not entitled to upgrades to pets that are broken? 
<br />

<br />
I do go on raids but just because I do not have the time to timesink 20+ hours in a quest to get a focus item does not mean that I should not be entitled to improvements to something that everyone will agree is broken.
<br />

<br />
Simply put this game should not be geared toward the elemental+ crowd. I am a business major and I will tell you right now that when all of your customers are complaining about factor A you can not say the answer is a change that is going to effect 20% of your customer base. 
<br />

<br />
You do that very long and you find yourself at the employment office looking for a new job. 
<br />

<br />
There should be more then one solution to this. Maybe start by adding a new focus item that is for high end content and then maybe down the line create a lower lvl version of this that would make everyone happy. 
<br />

<br />
I am really not trying to create a problem here. I just want an answer to this problem that will help both the hard core raider and the casual player alike. I think everyone would agree that the current focus items are not enough and to be honest with you even if I could get them and wanted to put the time in I do not know if I would. The improvements are so small that it just does not seem worth the time sink. That is the problem for everyone after all.
<br />

<br />
Remember one thing. no matter if you are casual or a hardcore raider we are all mages here and we should stand together on this. We all agree that this is broken and needs to be fixed. Find a solution that will make the mage community as a whole happy and we get the goal that we all want.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
